FBIS4-26046 "drchi117_k_94013" FBIS-CHI-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Leadership Marks 45th Anniversary of GUANGMING DAILY Leadership Marks 45th Anniversary of GUANGMING DAILY OW1606142594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1417 GMT 16 Jun 94 OW1606142594 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, June 16 (XINHUA) -- A forum was held in the Great Hall of the People here today to mark the 45th anniversary of the publication of GUANGMING DAILY, one of China's major newspapers mainly serving the intelligentsia. Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi and Li Ruihuan sent their inscriptions for its anniversary to encourage the newspaper to play an active role in uniting intellectuals, upholding fine traditions, attaching importance to education and science, respecting knowledge and talents, and advocating truth. Ding Guangen, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, telephoned GUANGMING DAILY to express his congratulations. Published in Beijing on June 16, 1949, GUANGMING DAILY is focused on economic and social issues that intellectuals are most keen on. To celebrate its 45th birthday, the newspaper has decided to build a small library in a village in Hebei Province with 3,900 books donated by its staff.
